# NS0394 Sync Error: A/P Approval Account Isn’t Set

If you see the error message **“NS0394 Sync Error: Expensify couldn’t mark NetSuite Expense Report ID [XXXXX] as paid because the A/P approval account isn’t set.”**, it means an Accounts Payable (A/P) account has not been configured in Expensify.

Without an A/P account selected, Expensify cannot mark reimbursed expense reports as paid in NetSuite.

---

## Why the NS0394 Sync Error Happens

The NS0394 sync error occurs when an **Accounts Payable account** is not selected in the Workspace’s NetSuite accounting settings.

The **Sync Reimbursed Reports** setting requires an A/P account in order to update payment status in NetSuite.

---

## How to Fix the NS0394 Sync Error

Follow the steps below to configure an Accounts Payable account.

---

## Step 1: Select an Accounts Payable Account in Expensify

On web:

1. Go to the **navigation tabs on the left** and select **Workspaces**.
2. Select your Workspace.
3. Select **Accounting**.
4. Select **Advanced**.
5. Locate the **Sync Reimbursed Reports** setting.
6. Choose an **Accounts Payable** account from the dropdown.
7. Click **Save**.

On mobile:

1. Tap the **navigation tabs on the bottom** and select **Workspaces**.
2. Select your Workspace.
3. Tap **Accounting**.
4. Tap **Advanced**.
5. Locate **Sync Reimbursed Reports**.
6. Select an **Accounts Payable** account.
7. Tap **Save**.

---

## Step 2: Create an A/P Account in NetSuite (If None Are Available)

If no Accounts Payable accounts appear in the dropdown:

1. Create an **Accounts Payable** account in NetSuite.
2. Return to Expensify.
3. Go to **Workspaces > [Workspace Name] > Accounting**.
4. Click the **three-dot icon** next to the NetSuite connection.
5. Click **Sync now**.

Once the sync completes:

1. Go back to **Accounting > Advanced**.
2. Select the newly available **Accounts Payable** account.
3. Click **Save**.

After saving the configuration, retry the export or payment sync.

---

# FAQ

## Does the NS0394 Sync Error affect all reimbursed reports?

Yes. Until an Accounts Payable account is selected, Expensify cannot mark reimbursed reports as paid in NetSuite.

## Do I need NetSuite admin access to fix the NS0394 Sync Error?

You may need appropriate NetSuite permissions to create a new Accounts Payable account if one does not already exist.
